Package: bulkKnk
Title: In Silico Virtual Knockout Engine for Bulk RNA-seq Cohorts
Version: 0.6.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "生信夜班侠",
           email = "admin@yida-alliance.org",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A robust computational framework to simulate gene knockouts in bulk transcriptomic cohorts. By integrating WGCNA for dimensionality reduction, GENIE3 for non-linear causal network inference, and Network Propagation dynamics, `bulkKnk` accurately predicts full-network transcriptomic responses to single-gene perturbations. It is particularly suited for exploring complex mechanisms such as chemoresistance in gastric cancer and tumor microenvironment remodeling.
